Essentia is an open-source C++ library for audio analysis and audio-based music
information retrieval released under the Affero GPL license. It contains an
extensive collection of reusable algorithms which implement audio input/output
functionality, standard digital signal processing blocks, statistical
characterization of data, and a large set of spectral, temporal, tonal and
high-level music descriptors. 

WWW: http://essentia.upf.edu